              ],
              "text": "Setup quality is B rather than A because the DC part of the thesis rhymes too closely with the FTTH boom-and-bust the company is still exiting. If DC is FTTH-in-disguise with a 3-5 year lag, the mix-shift thesis compounds rather than diversifies the cyclical risk. ESA needs to pressure-test this directly — the question is not whether DC growth is real, but whether the revenue quality is durable past the hyperscaler capex cycle."
